<ul>
<li>XPCOM (<b>XP</b> = cross platform)</li>
 <ul>
  <li>Component based architecture.</li>
   <ul>
    <li>Components are dynamically registered with a cross platform registry.</li>
    <li>Component retrieval is accomplished via do_CreateInstance() and do_GetService().</li>
   </ul>
  <li>Similar to COM, however, it does not support...</li>
   <ul>
    <li>DCOM-like cross-process proxying.</li>
   </ul>
  <li>Reference counting memory management model.</li>
  <li>nsISupports (functionally equivalent to IUnknown)</li>
   <ul>
    <li>QueryInterface(), AddRef(), Release()</li>
   </ul>
 </ul>

<li>Utility/convenience classes</li>
 <ul>
  <li>nsA[C]String - root Mozilla abstract string class.</li>
  <li>nsCOMPtr is XPCOM's "smart pointer."</li>
 </ul>
</ul>
